http://online.wsj.com/article_email/0,,SB105821991056891800,00.html   Manifesto Warns of Dangers  Associated With an Empire  POLITICAL CAPITAL                                                                             By ALAN MURRAY         in the Wall street journal                                                                     An unusual manifesto is circulating through the e-mail boxes of prominent Washingtonians from an ad hoc group calling itself the "Committee for the Republic." Its five sponsors include conservative C. Boyden Gray, a White House lawyer in the first Bush administration; Chas. W. Freeman, a former ambassador to Saudi Arabia; and Stephen Cohen, a senior fellow at the Brookings Institution.The manifesto is a work in progress, its authors say. But the goal is clear: to educate Americans about the dangers of empire.  for more... http://online.wsj.com/article_email/0,,SB105821991056891800,00.html